Goya (DK Eyewitness)
Dorling Kindersley | 1999 | ISBN: 0789448777 | English | 72 pages | PDF | 15 MB

Explore Goya's life and art, and the influences that shaped his work. DK gives a new look to the series that forever changed the nonfiction genre and set the standard for highly informative visual guides. This volume, and those to follow in future seasons, forms part of an indispensable library for the whole family. Focusing on the life and work of Goya, this book uses superb full-color photography to bring the artist's work to life and to explore the conditions and motivations that inspired it
